# vLLM RHEL10 Project Rule

## Scope and defaults
- This repo targets RHEL10 hosts and NVIDIA GPUs.
- Runtime default is Podman-compatible flow; Docker CLI may be Podman emulation.
- vLLM container base is Ubuntu 22.04 due to current RHEL10 image constraints.

## Script and path conventions
- Keep executable entrypoints in `scripts/`; wrappers in `runner/`, `stats/`, and `initialize/`.
- Every Bash entrypoint must resolve `ROOT_DIR` and `cd "$ROOT_DIR"` before relative paths.
- Do not reference root scripts that do not exist; prefer `scripts/<name>.sh`.

## Bash quality guardrails
- Use `#!/usr/bin/env bash` and `set -euo pipefail`.
- Quote variable expansions and paths (`"$VAR"`), especially for model paths and logs.
- Prefer idempotent checks (existence tests) before remove/build/run operations.
- Never use destructive git commands from automation scripts.

## Python and API expectations
- Keep Python scripts CLI-friendly and configurable via env vars (e.g., base URL, model, max tokens).
- For test clients, respect server `MAX_MODEL_LEN`; avoid hardcoded token outputs that can exceed context.
- Keep OpenAI-compatible checks explicit: `/v1/models` before generation tests.

## GPU and runtime checks
- Validate `nvidia-smi` on host and inside container runtime before starting vLLM.
- Preserve support for both real Docker and Podman-emulated Docker.
- Favor conservative memory knobs on 12GB VRAM (`float16`, reduced `max-model-len`, low batch/seq).

## Documentation expectations
- Keep commands in docs aligned with actual script locations under `scripts/`.
- If script layout changes, update wrappers and README examples in the same change.
